                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.24/159: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-25T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 25, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Honduran Government has ordered 450,000 cartridges for army rifles from the
                    Remington Arms Company to be shipped from New York to Tela consigned Minister of
                    War Government Honduras.</p>
                <p>Referring to Department’s instruction No. 117, March 20, license for export
                    should be approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
